checkUpkeep.t.sol
├─ given the contract is paused
│  └─ it should revert
└─ given the contract is not paused
   ├─ given the asset out does not have configured asset params
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ give the asset out has configured params
      └─ given an auction is live
         ├─ when the auction is ended
         │  ├─ it should include the auctioned asset to the ended auction list
         │  └─ when the asset out price is not valid
         │     └─ it should return an empty eligible assets list
         ├─ when the auction is not ended
         │  └─ given the auctioned asset balance is zero
         │     └─ it should include the auctioned asset to the ended auction list
         └─ given an auction is not live
            ├─ when an auctionable asset price is stale
            │  └─ it should not include the auctionable asset to the eligible assets list
            └─ when an auctionable asset price is not stale
               ├─ given an auctionable asset's available balance USD value is greater or equal to the minimum auction size
               │  └─ it should include the auctionable asset to the eligible assets list
               ├─ when the eligible assets index is not equal to the allowlisted assets length
               │  └─ it should update the eligible assets list length
               ├─ when the ended auctions index is not equal to the allowlisted assets length
               │  └─ it should updated the ended auctions list length
               ├─ when both eligible assets and ended auctions list are empty
               │  ├─ it should return false
               │  └─ it should return an empty perform data
               └─ when either eligible assets or ended auctions list is not empty
                  ├─ it should return true
                  └─ it should return the abi encoded lists
